  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div dir=\"auto\" class=\"body markup\">\n   <p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A web page loads in under a second. In that second, a single user request may have passed through roughly ten distinct systems on its way to and from the database. The page feels fast because of how those systems are arranged. Each layer absorbs as much traffic as it can before passing the rest along. Taken together, the layers form a funnel, with most traffic handled long before it reaches the bottom.</p>\n   <p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Understanding what each layer does to narrow that funnel can lead to a better grasp of each component of a modern web stack.</p>\n   <p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In this article, we follow the journey of a web request one hop at a time. At each stop, we ask two questions. What is this layer doing, and what trade-off is it making? The journey starts before the request has fully left the browser, and latency is spent at every hop.</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260604194251_d486fdf8-79de-429b-b453-67a3af15caed_2250x2624.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture><img src=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260604194251_d486fdf8-79de-429b-b453-67a3af15caed_2250x2624.png\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/d486fdf8-79de-429b-b453-67a3af15caed_2250x2624.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1698,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:133134,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/200598985?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd486fdf8-79de-429b-b453-67a3af15caed_2250x2624.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">DNS\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/200598985/dns\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "本文追踪一个 Web 请求在现代架构的每一层中的流转，解释了从 DNS 到数据库每个组件的作用与权衡。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "本文追踪一个 Web 请求在现代架构的每一层中的流转，解释了从 DNS 到数据库每个组件的作用与权衡。",
  "summary": "本文通过单个 Web 请求的旅程，解释了现代 Web 系统的分层架构。文章从一个前提开始：一次不到一秒的页面加载，涉及大约十个不同的系统，它们像漏斗一样排列，每一层在将剩余流量传递下去之前先吸收一部分。接着，作者逐一讲解每一跳——DNS、CDN、负载均衡器、Web 服务器、应用服务器、缓存、数据库等——在每个节点询问该层的作用以及它所做的权衡。整篇文章以导览的形式展开，强调延迟消耗在每一跳中，理解每一层的功能和取舍是掌握整个技术栈的关键。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "现代 Web 架构是一个分层漏斗，在每一层吸收流量。",
      "explanation": "每一层（DNS、CDN、负载均衡器等）在将剩余流量传递到下游之前，尽可能多地处理流量，从而减轻深层系统的负载。"
    },
    {
      "point": "请求路径中的每一跳都会引入延迟，并涉及一种权衡。",
      "explanation": "文章强调，理解每一层的功能及其固有的取舍（例如，缓存与新鲜度、分布式与一致性）对于系统设计至关重要。"
    },
    {
      "point": "这次导览涵盖了从浏览器到数据库的大约十个不同系统。",
      "explanation": "从 DNS 解析开始，到数据库结束，文章系统地解释了处理单个用户请求时每个组件的作用。"
    }
  ],
  "keyQuotes": [
    "每一层在将剩余流量传递下去之前，都会尽可能多地吸收流量。这些层共同形成一个漏斗，大多数流量在到达底部之前就已经被处理完毕。",
    "在每一站，我们都会问两个问题：这一层在做什么？它做出了什么权衡？"
  ],
